# Kai Swimlane DSL

Use this DSL inside a fenced block tagged `kai-swimlane` (full diagram) or `kai-swimlane-parts` (blocks/props only).

## Full document (required markers)

```txt
@kai-swimlane

/title/
My Process

/role/
<sales>
label: Sales;
background-color: #e6f2ff;

/line/
[sales: Receive order]

@end
```

## Sections

- `/title/` — diagram title
- `/role/` — lanes: `<roleId>` then `label:`, `text-color:`, `background-color:`, `icon:`
- `/block/` — reusable step styles: `shape:`, colors, `icon: #lucide-name`
- `/prop/` — document chips attached to steps
- `/line/` — flow: `[roleId: label]`, branches (`if` / `elseif` / `else` / `endif`)

## Property lines

In `/role/`, `/block/`, and `/prop/`, each property line must end with `;`.

## Step line

```txt
[roleId: Step label] <optionalBlockId>
label: Optional;
desc: Optional description;
props: PROP1, PROP2;
```

## Parts-only fence

For template fragments without lanes or flow, use `kai-swimlane-parts` with only `/block/` and/or `/prop/` content.

## Markdown preview

Install the bundled VS Code extension (see plugin `README.md`) so `kai-swimlane` fences render in Markdown preview.
